17/12/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- Minister of State for Defence Theodore Kotsonis and his counterpart from Belgrade, Vukasin Maras, signed three defence co-operation agreements on Tuesday (16 December). The deals provide for the appointment of a Greek military adviser at the defence ministry in Belgrade and co-operation between the hydrographic services of their respective navies. According to Kotsonis, Greece and Serbia-Montenegro also agreed to "fight the actions of extremist nationalists, attempts at division in the Balkans, organised crime, trafficking and corruption". In addition, they discussed Serbia-Montenegro's aspirations for membership in the EU and NATO. (AFP - 16/12/03)
